Spreads on bonds issued by Telsa Inc. TSLA, +4.37% widened sharply on Monday, as global stocks tanked amid a steep decline in crude prices as Saudi Arabia and Russia started a price war. Tesla's 5.300% notes that mature in August of 2025 were 137 basis points wider on the day for a spread of 592 basis points over comparable Treasurys. The bonds were trading at 95 cents on the dollar, down more than five points from Friday. Tesla shares, meanwhile, were down 7%. The stock remains up 130% in the last 12 months, while the S&P 500 SPX, +0.28% has gained 2%. 